<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-02-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-02-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="1610" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1610">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.93/62.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Simpich</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cananea</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-26">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 26, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Situation in Canaea temporarily relieved, soldiers having been
                                allowed and order restored, though feeling against Chinese is still
                                intense. On 24th one Chinese laundry was looted and two Chinese
                                stoned and slightly injured by mob. Governor Maytorena, in reply to
                                Consular Agent Montague’s demand has telegraphed assurances that
                                orders have been given to Cananea authorities for the protection of
                                foreign lives and property but the attitude of the municipal
                                officials towards Chinese in particular is such that full dependence
                                could not be placed in their promises should the situation become
                                critical.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Simpich</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>